## babylon powerbi dataset datasource update-credentials

To test the new commands proceed as follow:
- Add or edit the following lines in `config/platforms/platform.yaml`
```yaml
# Powerbi api scope
powerbi_api_scope: "https://analysis.windows.net/powerbi/api/.default"
```
- Add or edit the following lines in `config/deployments/deploy.yaml`
```yaml
# Powerbi workspace id
powerbi_workspace_id: ""
```

You can grab a `dataset id` for testing using `babylon powerbi dataset get-all`.
Then grab the `datasource id` and `gateway id` using `babylon powerbi dataset datasource get [dataset_id]`

### Commands

```bash
babylon powerbi dataset datasource update-credentials [datasource-id] -g [gateway-id]
```
Should update datasource credentials for the given datasource.
Can be checked in the powerBI web app.
